re the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Baron Robert FitzPayne of Poorstock was born about 1144, in Devon, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Sybil de Percy."},"et":{"about 1144–":"umbes 1144–Surnud","1148–Female":"1148–Surnud","1170–Female":"1170–Surnud","1144–Male":"1144–Surnud","1148":"1148","1144":"1144","about 1144":"umbes 1144","1170":"1170",",Devon,England.":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1144–":"noin 1144–Kuollut","1148–Female":"1148–Kuollut","1170–Female":"1170–Kuollut","1144–Male":"1144–Kuollut","1148":"1148","1144":"1144","about 1144":"noin 1144","1170":"1170",",Devon,England.":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Devon, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1144–":"environ 1144–Décédé","1148–Female":"1148–Décédée","1170–Female":"1170–Décédée","1144–Male":"1144–Décédé","1148":"1148","1144":"1144","about 1144":"environ 1144","1170":"1170",",Devon,England.":"Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Devon, England":"Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Baron Robert FitzPayne of Poorstock est né environ 1144, à Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Sybil de Percy."},"de":{"about 1144–":"um 1144–Verstorben","1148–Female":"1148–Verstorben","1170–Female":"1170–Verstorben","1144–Male":"1144–Verstorben","1148":"1148","1144":"1144","about 1144":"um 1144","1170":"1170",",Devon,England.":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Baro